race.comment: Lightly raced mare OVERTOOK (9) is back after an 11-month absence. Has only raced twice, with a win on debut then a close third over third trip at Wyong before the break. Trialled well at Kembla recently and looks ready to make a positive return. CALIDO MAGIC (4) has been racing well for some time without winning. Left with too much to do under a big weight at Kempsey last start. Gets in with 3.5kgs less today and over his pet trip can play a significant role. PRINCESS CRUIZER (6) has attacked the line with gusto at her last couple, both over 900m at Newcastle. Needs this trip and from a good gate will get every chance. Speedy filly LULL (10) is back after a 20-week spell. Has raced just three times, and only once on a good track for an all-the-way win over this distance at Kembla. Can cross and give backers a sight. GOGMAGOG (2) is at his best over five furlongs. Drawn to enjoy a lovely run and should be thereabouts.
